main event: An unidentified aerial observation was reported on 1 January 1960 at Moron AB, Spain.
interesting points: The observation lasted for approximately 5 minutes, and the object was seen for 5 seconds., The object was described as round or teardrop-shaped, about the size of a nickel at arm's length., Clear skies with good visibility were reported at the time of the sighting., Observers speculated the object resembled a space vehicle reentering the atmosphere due to its slow speed and intense light., No photographs were included in the report.
sighted object: a round or teardrop shaped object emitting intense light
